arXiv.abstract:
In various extensions of the Standard Model a neutrino can have nontrivial electromagnetic properties. In particular, a neutrino can be an electrically millicharged particle. This generates additional contributions to the neutrino electromagnetic interactions. Using the new limit on the neutrino magnetic moment recently obtained by the GEMMA experiment on measurements of the reactor antineutrino scattering off electrons we get the upper bound on the neutrino electric millicharge $\mid q_{
u} \mid < 1.5 	imes 10^{-12} e_0$. We also predict that with the expected progress in constraining the neutrino magnetic moment in the considered experiment the upper bound on the neutrino millicharge can be reduced to $\mid q_{
u} \mid < 3.7 	imes 10^{-13}e_0$ and even further to the level $\mid q_{
u} \mid < 2 	imes 10^{-13}e_0$ within several years.

